[{"_id":"c18e8250-b4f0-3481-9dd8-72f4dc8be01b","authorName":"Anonymous","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"It is probably an API design error to not make the ID an Int64.  \r\n\r\nThere was a similar problem with Environment.TickCount which wrapped ever 30 days or so. Flawed by design.","postId":"2013_03_a-few-words-on-taskid-and-93a06673-f1ea-3a1d-89a9-0c8889ad009c","replyTo":"","date":"2013-03-22T19:51:10Z","timestamp":1363981870,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"19b3673b-7864-3e01-b92e-302a656d2119","authorName":"David Bakin","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"24588aa575ef56fc97cb3fae574a827d","message":"I wish they weren't lazy - in IntelliTrace you see a bunch of Task \"<unknown id=\"\">\" Started events with no particular way to know how to match them up to anything.","postId":"2013_03_a-few-words-on-taskid-and-93a06673-f1ea-3a1d-89a9-0c8889ad009c","replyTo":"","date":"2014-06-27T16:03:34Z","timestamp":1403885014,"authorUserId":"disqus:davidbakin"},{"_id":"247db797-5fdb-3cbb-b1d6-3c17ebaa72d8","authorName":"Kelly Elton","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"599b8f5dc21d1e47f76449252caad960","message":"You can actually boil that IdManager class down quite a bit. Works great with lots of threads.\r\n\r\npublic static class IdManager<tag>  \r\n{  \r\n public static int _lastId = 0;\r\n\r\n public static int GetId(ref int id)  \r\n {  \r\n return id == 0 ? id = Interlocked.Increment(ref _lastId) : id;  \r\n }  \r\n}","postId":"2013_03_a-few-words-on-taskid-and-93a06673-f1ea-3a1d-89a9-0c8889ad009c","replyTo":"","date":"2017-01-13T23:13:38Z","timestamp":1484349218,"authorUserId":"disqus:skylabsonline"},{"_id":"09350fd7-9cdb-3189-9d17-c085d1da5626","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"In long-running apps, it is possible for ids to roll over. This one will return a 0 id when that happens.","postId":"2013_03_a-few-words-on-taskid-and-93a06673-f1ea-3a1d-89a9-0c8889ad009c","replyTo":"247db797-5fdb-3cbb-b1d6-3c17ebaa72d8","date":"2017-01-14T14:53:15Z","timestamp":1484405595,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}]